reviews.text: A country station, with a better train service than it deserves. There is nothing here except a small and ugly modern village -called Flexford, not Wanborough. No pub, shop or anywhere to eat.

Taking the train to Guildford is quick just one stop and each train arrives 18 and 48 minutes past the hour. 

Unfortunately there is no disabled access for  the platform to Guildford.

Hard pressed to call this more than a halt than a station. No step free access is available for trains heading towards Guildford which is very annoying. However to give credit, the footbridge has very shallow steps up. Only a single ticket machine is available and minimal seating and shelter too. Also no ticket office either.
